
[1]guy

   GUY, n. gi. In marine affairs, a rope used to keep a heavy body steady
   while hoisting or lowering; also, a tackle to confine a boom
   forwards,when a vessel is going large, and to prevent the sail from
   gybing. Guy is also a large slack rope, extending from the head of the
   main-mast to that of the fore-mast, to sustain a tackle for loading or
   unloading.
